Chidiebube Okeoma, Owerri The race for the emergence of the next deputy speaker of the Imo State House of Assembly has intensified following the emergence of a new governor in the state. Our correspondent learnt that four lawmakers: Authur Egwim (Ideato North), Obinna Okwara (Nkwerre), Chyna Iwuanyanwu (Nwangele) and Nelson Ezerioha (Oru West) are in the race to emerge the next deputy speaker. It was also learnt that the four lawmakers had advanced their campaigns in the camp of Governor Hope Uzodinma. It was gathered that following the emergence of Uzodinma as governor, the position of the deputy speaker will go to Orlu zone, in line with an arrangement in the House. Our correspondent learnt that the Majority Leader’s position will now go to Owerri zone in keeping fate with the arrangements in the House. A source said, “Four lawmakers from Orlu zone are jostling to emerge the next deputy speaker of the Imo State House of Assembly. “They have advanced their ambitions and are poaching the allies of the new governor. “The slot of the majority leader will now go to Owerri zone. This is the arrangement in the Assembly. “ The Assembly will on Tuesday, January 21 reconvene after a one-month Christmas and New Year break. Copyright PUNCH.
